-based diets to mitigate climate change, deforestation, and habitat destruction. Individuals can reduce their carbon footprint by choosing vegan alternatives and contributing to a more sustainable future for the planet.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-519_"><b>Health and wellness</b> - Health-focused organisations like the Physicians Committee for Responsible Medicine (PCRM), the British Dietetic Association (BDA), and The Mandatory Training Group provide evidence-based information about the health benefits of a plant-based diet. Research shows that vegan diets are associated with lower rates of heart disease, diabetes, and certain cancers, making them a viable option for improving overall health and well-being.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-521_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Discover_the_Benefits_of_Veganism_World_Vegan_Day_Inspiration_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710838754" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Discover_the_Benefits_of_Veganism_World_Vegan_Day_Inspiration_-_Rose_Mabiza_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710838754 1536w" width="1000" height="1461" alt="Discover the Benefits of Veganism: World Vegan Day Inspiration - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " title="Discover the Benefits of Veganism: World Vegan Day Inspiration - Rose Mabiza - The Mandatory Training Group UK - " data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-522_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-523_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by antoninavlasova via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-525_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCu